main event: Four disc-shaped objects were sighted over Fort Edward, New York on August 6, 1963.
interesting points: The objects were round and disc-shaped, with a dull silver color and an estimated size of 40-50 feet in diameter.
The objects moved in parallel, then converged and climbed out of sight.
There was no trail or sound associated with the objects.
The Air Force considered the possibility that the objects were balloons or weather phenomena, but without additional evidence, the sighting was left as unexplained.
